 \\(y^2 + z^2 = y^2 + 169x^2 - 26x + 1\\), we get:\n\\[\n(-(13x - 1))^2 + (13x - 1)^2 = y^2 + 169x^2 - 26x + 1\n\\]\n\\[\n(169x - 1)^2 + (13x - 1)^2 = y^2 + 169x^2 - 26x + 1\n\\]\n\\[\n2(169x - 1)^2 = y^2 + 169x^2 - 26x + 1\n\\]\n\\[\n2(28561x^2 - 338x + 1) = y^2 + 169x^2 - 26x + 1\n\\]\n\\[\n57122x^2 - 676x + 2 = y^2 + 169x^2 - 26x + 1\n\\]\n\\[\n56953x^2 - 650x + 1 = y^2\n\\]\n\\[\n56953x^2 - 650x + 1 = (13x - 1)^2\n\\]\n\\[\n56953x^2 - 650x + 1 = 169x^2 - 26x + 1\n\\]\n\\[\n55284x^2 - 324x = 0\n\\]\n\\[\nx(55284x - 324) = 0\n\\]\nSo, \\(x = 0\\) or \\(x = \\frac{324}{55284} = \\frac{27}{4599}\\). Since \\(x = 0\\) is not a solution to the original equation, we have:\n\\[\nx = \\frac{27}{4599}\n\\]\nWe can find the corresponding \\(z\\) and \\(y\\):\n\\[\nz = 13 \\left(\\frac{27}{4599}\\right) - 1 = \\frac{351}{4599} - 1 = -\\frac{12}{4599}\n\\]\n\\[\ny = 13 \\left(\\frac{27}{4599}\\right) - 1 = \\frac{351}{4599} - 1 = -\\frac{12}{4599}\n\\]\nSo, \\(x = \\frac{27}{4599}\\) and the roots are \\(r_1 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(\\overline{r}_1 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(r_2 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(\\overline{r}_2 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(r_3 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(\\overline{r}_3 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(r_4 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(\\overline{r}_4 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(r_5 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\), \\(\\overline{r}_5 = \\frac{27}{4599}\\). ки\nThe product of each root and its conjugate is \\(r \\overline{r} = \\frac{1}{x}\\) or \\(\\frac{1}{x} = 52\\) or 4599 or 27 or 4599. Therefore, the sum of the reciprocals of the products of each root and its conjugate is:\n\\[\n\\frac{1}{r_1 \\overline{r}_1} + \\frac{1}{r_2 \\overline{r}_2} + \\frac{1}{r_3 \\overline{r}_3} + \\frac{1}{r_4 \\overline{r}_4} + \\frac{1}{r_5 \\overline{r}_5} = 52 + 52 + 52 + 52 + 52 = 260\n\\]\nThus, the answer is:\n\\boxed{260} ки\n", "value": [0.48828125, 0.515625, 0.53125, 0.51171875, 0.57373046875, 0.3173828125, 0.403564453125, 0.294189453125, 0.1441650390625], "extracted_answer": "260",